To her there was beauty everywhere and in every little thing. It was her job to show that beauty to others.
"Lord have mercy," she said. "Lord have some motherfucking mercy on me."
"I've got a steady gig," I told her. "Deodorant commercials."
“When hell freezes over,” she snapped, furious with herself as well as him.
He froze and stared straight ahead.
“That doesn’t sound so bad,” I said. “You were talking about needing a new sketch pad.”
That thought made Tally's skin crawl  that the girl would soon be a bubblehead: pretty, beautiful, and happy. And monumentally clueless.
